{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584193","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584193"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:41:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:41:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14428"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14428","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14428"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.68,0.06,0.06,0.1,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7123"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"113869"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7123","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7123"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14428"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"95888"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"12"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"29"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"4906"},{"type":"tags","id":"4907"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4954"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4991"},{"type":"tags","id":"5981"},{"type":"tags","id":"11622"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11638"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"17020"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17162"},{"type":"contributions","id":"47255"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"113869","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/113869"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ERheumatic fever is an immune-mediated inflammatory condition that can follow untreated group A streptococcal pharyngitis. The Jones Criteria are used to standardise the diagnosis of acute rheumatic fever across populations, including in high-incidence settings in Australia such as remote Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander communities.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a major criterion of the Jones Criteria for diagnosing acute rheumatic fever?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Migratory polyarthritis","Fever","Arthralgia","Prolonged PR interval on electrocardiogram","Elevated erythrocyte sedimentation rate"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe Jones Criteria classify clinical features into major and minor categories to aid diagnosis of acute rheumatic fever after evidence of preceding group A streptococcal infection. In Australia, awareness is critical due to higher incidence in some regions and among Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples. Diagnosis generally requires two major criteria, or one major plus two minor criteria, together with evidence of a preceding group A streptococcal infection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA helpful way to remember this is using the \u0027JONES\u0027 mnemonic:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EJ\u003C/strong\u003Eoints (migratory polyarthritis)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EO\u003C/strong\u003Eh my heart (carditis)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EN\u003C/strong\u003Eodules (subcutaneous)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EE\u003C/strong\u003Erythema marginatum\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ES\u003C/strong\u003Eydenham chorea\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMigratory polyarthritis\u003C/strong\u003E is a major criterion and commonly presents early, affecting large joints in a migratory pattern.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFever\u003C/strong\u003E is a minor criterion and supports the diagnosis when combined with other features.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArthralgia\u003C/strong\u003E is a minor criterion and should be distinguished from objective arthritis, which is major.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProlonged PR interval on electrocardiogram\u003C/strong\u003E is a minor criterion reflecting conduction system involvement but is not itself a major manifestation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EElevated erythrocyte sedimentation rate\u003C/strong\u003E (or C-reactive protein) is a minor criterion indicating systemic inflammation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Major Jones criteria are carditis, migratory polyarthritis, chorea, erythema marginatum and subcutaneous nodules.","Minor Jones criteria are fever, arthralgia, raised acute phase reactants and prolonged PR interval on electrocardiogram."],"references":["Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. Robbins Basic Pathology (10th ed.). 2017. Elsevier - Health Sciences Division","Smith MT, Zurynski Y, Lester-Smith D, Elliott E, Carapetis J. Rheumatic fever - identification, management and secondary prevention. Aust Fam Physician. 2012 Jan-Feb;41(1-2):31-5. PMID: 22276281.","Gewitz MH, Baltimore RS, Tani LY, Sable CA, Shulman ST, Carapetis J, Remenyi B, Taubert KA, Bolger AF, Beerman L, Mayosi BM, Beaton A, Pandian NG, Kaplan EL; American Heart Association Committee on Rheumatic Fever, Endocarditis, and Kawasaki Disease of the Council on Cardiovascular Disease in the Young. Revision of the Jones Criteria for the diagnosis of acute rheumatic fever in the era of Doppler echocardiography: a scientific statement from the American Heart Association. Circulation. 2015 May 19;131(20):1806-18. doi: 10.1161/CIR.0000000000000205. Epub 2015 Apr 23. Erratum in: Circulation. 2020 Jul 28;142(4):e65. doi: 10.1161/CIR.0000000000000889. PMID: 25908771."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"95888"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14428"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"95888","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/95888"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-14T08:58:39+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-14T08:59:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7123"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"113869"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"12","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/12"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc4b","name":"Rheumatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:47+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"29","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/29"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2c","n